reviewText: A contemporary of Robert Johnson and very good original blues artist lives well into the third millenium and recounts his incredible life and adventures over nearly 5 score years. Come jam with this grand daddy of blues.

it's was ok.. interesting moments of discussion but did not have me riveted to it..
I might watch it one more time..
What a treat to see Honeyboy get his props!  He performed with the men and women who framed the Blues genre in the early 20th century.
This is a good DVD if you like blues history. The only downside is that Honey Boy is hard to understand.
